  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "FM (voice 1, fmRatio=1.5 = perfect fifth carrier) + Additive (voice 2, rich partials). HAMMER=+0.5 — light-to-medium LOVE. The consonant FM ratio (3:2) predisposes the voice pair toward harmonic lock even before LOVE is applied. Additive's even partials then fuse with FM's sidebands into a single, extraordinarily rich harmonic series. This is OUIE at its most overtly beautiful — a pad that rewards long held notes.",
  "tags": [
    "ouie",
    "fm",
    "additive",
    "harmony",
    "consonant",
    "love",
    "pad",
    "aether",
    "harmonic-lock"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OUIE — The Hammerhead",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "The ratio 3:2 is the perfect fifth. In FM it is always consonant.",
      "Additive adds the even harmonics FM leaves out. Together: a complete spectrum.",
      "HAMMER=+0.5 is where harmony becomes physics."
    ],
    "revelation": null,
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "Try raising fmRatio1 from 1.5 to 2.0 (octave) or 3.0 (octave + fifth) and rehear how the LOVE interaction changes. Consonant ratios always arrive at beauty. Inharmonic ratios (2.3, 3.7) create tension even in LOVE.",
    "diagnosis": "Demonstrates that HAMMER LOVE is not just a blend — it is a spectral interaction that depends on the source material. FM with consonant carrier ratio + additive is the most harmonically generous pairing in the OUIE engine. Suitable for orchestral-style pads, harmonic drones, ambient music."
  },
